1
00:00:04,238 --> 00:00:06,674
(Minseok) ⟨I lost my Japanese parents when I was young →

2
00:00:06,741 --> 00:00:09,677
I was adopted by a Korean chaebol family→

3
00:00:09,744 --> 00:00:13,180
Just as I was about to take over as president after my father...⟩

4
00:00:13,247 --> 00:00:18,252
>> Korean

5
00:00:19,253 --> 00:00:20,688
(Kyonhwa) Get out!

6
00:00:20,755 --> 00:00:24,258
(Minseok) ⟨I was chased out of Korea after being accused of embezzlement⟩

7
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:27,695
(Momoko) Are you okay?

8
00:00:27,762 --> 00:00:30,197
(Minseok) ⟨Meeting Dr. Momoko, a doctor at the clinic→

9
00:00:30,264 --> 00:00:33,701
Go to the children's cafeteria run by the clinic⟩

10
00:00:33,768 --> 00:00:36,704
(Mizushima) The head office told me that I don't have to give you any special duties.

11
00:00:36,771 --> 00:00:38,706
That's what they say. (Minseok) Huh?

12
00:00:38,773 --> 00:00:46,714
>> Korean

13
00:00:46,781 --> 00:00:48,716
(Momoko) Mr. Minseok?

14
00:00:48,783 --> 00:00:52,219
(Minseok) ⟨I thought I had lost everything→

15
00:00:52,286 --> 00:00:55,723
I was starting to find a quiet and certain place to live⟩

16
00:00:55,790 --> 00:01:06,734
♪～

17
00:01:09,737 --> 00:01:17,178
>> [Ambulance siren]

18
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:21,248
(Minseok) [Dad! mother! ]

19
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:25,686
(Passerby) [I feel sorry for your parents]

20
00:01:25,753 --> 00:01:28,756
(Nurse) [It's okay to cry without holding back]

21
00:01:34,261 --> 00:01:46,707
[Girl's cry]

22
00:01:46,774 --> 00:01:49,210
〔father…〕

23
00:01:49,276 --> 00:02:09,163
〔cry〕

24
00:02:09,230 --> 00:02:12,166
〔cry〕

25
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:17,171
[Two people crying]

26
00:02:17,238 --> 00:02:21,242
(Minseok) [Father...] >> [Girl's cry]

27
00:03:12,726 --> 00:03:15,663
(Momoko) Ah! (Minseok) Ah. (Momoko) Sorry, I fell asleep.

28
00:03:15,729 --> 00:03:18,232
(Minseok) Ah, I fell asleep too.

29
00:03:20,734 --> 00:03:22,670
(Momoko) Ah, that's right, this.

30
00:03:22,736 --> 00:03:25,172
Ah... it's getting cold.

31
00:03:25,239 --> 00:03:27,241
(Minseok) Ah, I'll eat it.

32
00:03:43,257 --> 00:03:45,259
(Minseok) I'm sorry.

33
00:03:51,265 --> 00:03:55,269
(Minseok) I'm sorry about earlier.

34
00:03:57,271 --> 00:04:06,213
〔cry〕

35
00:04:08,716 --> 00:04:10,718
(Momoko) Please don't apologize.

36
00:04:14,221 --> 00:04:16,223
(Momoko) Did something happen?

37
00:04:27,234 --> 00:04:30,738
(Minseok) No, nothing.

38
00:04:35,242 --> 00:04:40,180
(Minseok) I was happy with everyone's feelings.

39
00:04:40,247 --> 00:05:13,647
♪～

40
00:05:13,714 --> 00:05:16,150
(Minseok) Thank you very much. (Momoko) No.

41
00:05:16,216 --> 00:05:18,152
take care.

42
00:05:18,218 --> 00:05:20,154
(Minseok) Well then. (Momoko) Well then.

43
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:29,229
♪～

44
00:05:32,232 --> 00:05:34,668
(Momoko) Minseok-san.

45
00:05:34,735 --> 00:05:37,171
that….

46
00:05:37,237 --> 00:05:42,242
There are words that I have always cherished.

47
00:05:46,246 --> 00:05:50,250
(Momoko) ``There is no tree that will not fall down even if you cut it 10 times.''

48
00:05:52,252 --> 00:05:57,691
I always remember these words when I feel like giving up.

49
00:05:57,758 --> 00:06:03,130
If you keep going again and again without giving up →

50
00:06:03,197 --> 00:06:05,699
Someday the tree will fall.

51
00:06:08,202 --> 00:06:13,207
I have lived my life supported by these words.

52
00:06:20,714 --> 00:06:23,650
(Minseok) Um...

53
00:06:23,717 --> 00:06:27,154
That word is...

54
00:06:27,221 --> 00:06:29,656
(Sound of door opening) (Kazami) I'm home.

55
00:06:29,723 --> 00:06:31,658
(Kazami) Oh, Minseok!

56
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:33,660
It was coming! (Minseok) Good evening.

57
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:35,662
(Momoko) Welcome back. >> I'm just glad.

58
00:06:35,729 --> 00:06:38,665
Donuts there are sold at half price.

59
00:06:38,732 --> 00:06:42,169
Would you like to eat 200 yen for 100 yen?

60
00:06:42,236 --> 00:06:45,672
(Minseok) Ah, I'm sorry, but today...

61
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:48,175
>> See you then. (Minseok) See you again.

62
00:06:48,242 --> 00:06:51,678
>> Yes, okay.

63
00:06:51,745 --> 00:06:55,682
(Sound of door opening and closing)

64
00:06:55,749 --> 00:07:03,624
♪～

65
00:07:03,690 --> 00:07:07,694
(Girl) [My father died]

66
00:07:09,196 --> 00:07:11,698
[I can't see you again]

67
00:07:15,202 --> 00:07:17,204
〔I miss you…〕

68
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:26,213
(Minseok) [Hey, do you know? ]

69
00:07:28,215 --> 00:07:31,218
[Character that will cheer you up]

70
00:07:35,222 --> 00:07:39,159
(Minseok) [There is no tree that will not fall after being cut 10 times]

71
00:07:39,226 --> 00:07:54,675
♪～

72
00:07:54,741 --> 00:07:58,178
(Minseok) 《Momoko-sensei...》

73
00:07:58,245 --> 00:08:01,181
《Why this word》

74
00:08:01,248 --> 00:08:16,196
♪～

75
00:08:17,698 --> 00:08:20,133
(Female) It was delicious. (Male) Ah hahaha…｡

76
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:23,136
Let's come here again for our wedding anniversary next year.

77
00:08:23,203 --> 00:08:25,706
That's right hahaha...

78
00:08:36,216 --> 00:08:42,656
Korean

79
00:08:42,723 --> 00:08:45,225
(Minseok) [Ah...]

80
00:09:07,180 --> 00:09:10,617
(Momoko) [“There is no tree that will not fall even after being cut 10 times”]

81
00:09:10,684 --> 00:09:15,622
[If you keep going again and again and again without giving up→

82
00:09:15,689 --> 00:09:18,191
Someday the tree will fall

83
00:09:34,708 --> 00:09:37,144
>>Are you kidding? (Minseok) I'm not kidding.

84
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:40,647
>>Because you're probably the deputy manager.

85
00:09:40,714 --> 00:09:42,649
(Minseok) I want to know because I'm the deputy manager.

86
00:09:42,716 --> 00:09:45,652
About this hotel from scratch.

87
00:09:45,719 --> 00:09:47,654
>> Starting from scratch...

88
00:09:47,721 --> 00:09:49,156
(Minseok) Please.

89
00:09:49,222 --> 00:09:51,725
>> No, no, no, no...

90
00:09:54,728 --> 00:09:57,731
Stop for a moment.

91
00:09:59,232 --> 00:10:01,668
(Mizushima) Stop it.

92
00:10:01,735 --> 00:10:05,172
Please stop!

93
00:10:05,238 --> 00:10:07,174
already….

94
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:10,677
If so, you should do whatever you like.

95
00:10:10,744 --> 00:10:13,180
(Minseok) Thank you.

96
00:10:13,246 --> 00:10:17,751
>> After all, you are doing this on your own.

97
00:10:19,252 --> 00:10:21,254
No shame!

98
00:10:23,757 --> 00:10:39,206
♪～

99
00:10:39,272 --> 00:10:43,276
(Minseok) 《I haven't cut 10 yet》

100
00:10:47,781 --> 00:10:51,785
(Minseok) 《Start from here again》

101
00:10:55,288 --> 00:10:57,724
(Minseok) Welcome.

102
00:10:57,791 --> 00:11:00,227
Welcome to Hwangeum Hotel.

103
00:11:00,293 --> 00:11:11,238
♪～

104
00:11:22,249 --> 00:11:31,191
>> Korean

105
00:11:31,258 --> 00:11:32,759
(Hisn) Huh.

106
00:12:21,241 --> 00:12:23,743
(Minseok) Please have a good time.

107
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:30,183
(Minseok) [“10 times”…]

108
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:36,690
[“There is no tree that can be cut 10 times and still not fall.”]

109
00:12:36,756 --> 00:12:39,192
(Y/N) [That's a Korean proverb.]

110
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:41,194
(Minseok) [Korean? 〕 (Excellent) 〔Yes〕

111
00:12:41,261 --> 00:12:45,699
[If you don't give up and express your feelings even if the girl you like dumps you →

112
00:12:45,765 --> 00:12:48,201
It means that it will definitely arrive.]

113
00:12:48,268 --> 00:12:50,203
(Minseok) [That's right]

114
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:53,206
>> [Ah, that's right Teru]

115
00:12:53,273 --> 00:12:55,275
(Minseok) [Hmm? ]

116
00:12:56,777 --> 00:12:58,712
>> [Father thinks]

117
00:12:58,778 --> 00:13:02,716
[Other things are the same]

118
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:06,653
[If you try hard and don't give up even if you fail once →

119
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:09,656
I'm sure your wish will come true.]

120
00:13:09,723 --> 00:13:13,727
[You can't give up on what you really want]

121
00:13:16,730 --> 00:13:18,165
(Minseok) [Yeah]

122
00:13:18,231 --> 00:13:21,668
>> [Remember this when you feel like you might not be able to do your best]

123
00:13:21,735 --> 00:13:25,672
[It's a spell that will cheer you up]

124
00:13:25,739 --> 00:13:27,240
(Minseok) [Yes! ]

125
00:13:28,742 --> 00:13:33,180
(Girl) Oh no, no, no...!

126
00:13:33,246 --> 00:13:36,683
(Minseok) Welcome, would you like some candy?

127
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:38,685
>> Oh, sorry.

128
00:13:38,752 --> 00:13:41,688
(Minseok) Which one do you like?

129
00:13:41,755 --> 00:13:43,690
This way?

130
00:13:43,757 --> 00:13:46,259
>> Thank you. (Minseok) That's unbelievable.

131
00:13:47,761 --> 00:13:50,263
Ah, I apologize for the inconvenience. (Staff) I apologize for the inconvenience.

132
00:13:53,767 --> 00:13:56,203
(Minseok) Se~no.

133
00:13:56,269 --> 00:13:58,772
Yes, thank you.

134
00:14:02,275 --> 00:14:04,144
(Natsume) What are you doing?

135
00:14:04,211 --> 00:14:07,147
(Minseok) Ah, for small children and people in wheelchairs →

136
00:14:07,214 --> 00:14:09,149
It was in a position that would get in the way.

137
00:14:09,216 --> 00:14:11,151
>>Ah, certainly.

138
00:14:11,218 --> 00:14:13,220
(Minseok) Welcome.

139
00:14:16,723 --> 00:14:18,725
>> Hey.

140
00:14:20,727 --> 00:14:24,164
What are you doing? >> Ah yes!

141
00:14:24,231 --> 00:14:26,666
(Male) The scenery outside is so wonderful →

142
00:14:26,733 --> 00:14:29,169
The food is delicious and I'm looking forward to it.

143
00:14:29,236 --> 00:14:31,171
(Minseok) Thank you. (Male) Thank you for your help.

144
00:14:31,238 --> 00:14:33,240
(Minseok) Thank you very much. (Male) Thank you.

145
00:14:39,246 --> 00:14:42,182
(Momoko) Minseok-san.

146
00:14:42,249 --> 00:14:44,184
(Minseok) Momoko Sensei.

147
00:14:44,251 --> 00:14:47,187
(Momoko) Hello. (Minseok) Hello, is that a house call?

148
00:14:47,254 --> 00:14:50,690
(Momoko) Yes, did something good happen?

149
00:14:50,757 --> 00:14:53,193
(Minseok) Huh? Why?

150
00:14:53,260 --> 00:14:56,196
(Momoko) My back feels relieved.

151
00:14:56,263 --> 00:14:58,198
(Minseok) Howa?

152
00:14:58,265 --> 00:15:00,700
(Momoko) I'm feeling excited.

153
00:15:00,767 --> 00:15:02,702
(Minseok) Is that so? (Momoko) Yes.

154
00:15:02,769 --> 00:15:05,639
Ah, today is Children's Cafeteria Day. (Minseok) Ah, I'm going to help out too.

155
00:15:05,705 --> 00:15:07,641
(Momoko) Hey, please go ahead.

156
00:15:07,707 --> 00:15:10,210
I'll be there as soon as it's finished, okay?

157
00:15:16,216 --> 00:15:17,651
(Momoko) Oh, what?

158
00:15:17,717 --> 00:15:20,153
(Minseok) Let's go. (Momoko) Wow, amazing, amazing!

159
00:15:20,220 --> 00:15:22,656
Wow! (Minseok) What do you think?

160
00:15:22,722 --> 00:15:25,659
(Momoko) Feels good! Amazing amazing!

161
00:15:25,725 --> 00:15:28,662
Thank you, Minseok-san, see you later.

162
00:15:28,728 --> 00:15:31,164
(Minseok) Take care. (Momoko) Yes!

163
00:15:31,231 --> 00:15:39,172
♪～

164
00:15:39,239 --> 00:15:41,174
(Minseok) Yes, please.

165
00:15:41,241 --> 00:15:43,176
(Child) Thank you.

166
00:15:43,243 --> 00:15:45,679
Will Minseok serve it again today?

167
00:15:45,745 --> 00:15:47,681
It's innovative. (Ryo) Hey! Yeah.

168
00:15:47,747 --> 00:15:50,183
(Mika) What is it? this.

169
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:53,186
(Mika) Ah, “tsukema”! “Tsukema”? what? that.

170
00:15:53,253 --> 00:15:54,688
False eyelashes.

171
00:15:54,754 --> 00:15:56,690
Ah! Mika-chan's favorite.

172
00:15:56,756 --> 00:15:58,692
Ah, I'm "Matsupa".

173
00:15:58,758 --> 00:16:01,695
"Matsupa" Yes.

174
00:16:01,761 --> 00:16:03,630
(Momoko) Thank you for waiting.

175
00:16:03,697 --> 00:16:05,632
(Minseok) Good.

176
00:16:05,699 --> 00:16:09,135
>>Do you like the chair? (Minseok) Yeah, I really liked it.

177
00:16:09,202 --> 00:16:11,137
>> Hey, I worked hard.

178
00:16:11,204 --> 00:16:13,640
It's me! It's me!

179
00:16:13,707 --> 00:16:15,642
(Momoko) Ah, hey, hey, hey...!

180
00:16:15,709 --> 00:16:17,644
(Minseok) Thank you everyone.

181
00:16:17,711 --> 00:16:19,646
I was so happy.

182
00:16:19,713 --> 00:16:21,648
(Momoko) Good for you, everyone. (Children) Yeah!

183
00:16:21,715 --> 00:16:24,651
Okay, then everyone.

184
00:16:24,718 --> 00:16:26,653
I'll enjoy having this.

185
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:29,723
(All) Itadakimasu.

186
00:16:34,227 --> 00:16:36,162
(Momoko) Hmm, delicious! It's delicious.

187
00:16:36,229 --> 00:16:38,665
(Child) It's delicious.

188
00:16:38,732 --> 00:16:42,669
(Mika) I'm going. Watch me. I'm going.

189
00:16:42,736 --> 00:16:44,671
Well then! (claps and cheers)

190
00:16:44,738 --> 00:16:48,174
(claps and cheers)

191
00:16:48,241 --> 00:16:50,176
(Momoko) Amazing!

192
00:16:50,243 --> 00:16:54,180
(Mika) Nothing.

193
00:16:54,247 --> 00:16:58,251
(Momoko) [“There is no tree that will not fall even after being cut 10 times”]

194
00:16:59,753 --> 00:17:01,688
(Minseok) Um...

195
00:17:01,755 --> 00:17:03,623
(Momoko) Yes.

196
00:17:03,690 --> 00:17:06,126
(Minseok) We were talking the other day...

197
00:17:06,192 --> 00:17:08,128
(Takuto) Everyone, please wait!

198
00:17:08,194 --> 00:17:10,630
(Child) Takuto! (Takuto) Hahaha...｡

199
00:17:10,697 --> 00:17:12,632
Ah, you came too.

200
00:17:12,699 --> 00:17:14,634
(Minseok) Hello. (Momoko) Good work.

201
00:17:14,701 --> 00:17:16,136
(Takuto) Hey!

202
00:17:16,202 --> 00:17:18,138
Hey, wait a minute, that's amazing!

203
00:17:18,204 --> 00:17:20,640
This is a new chair.

204
00:17:20,707 --> 00:17:23,643
Or rather, aren't you more enthusiastic than me?

205
00:17:23,710 --> 00:17:26,646
>> Hehehe…｡ (Takuto) Ah, it’s you guys after all!

206
00:17:26,713 --> 00:17:29,149
Let me make it again. >> Hurry...

207
00:17:29,215 --> 00:17:31,718
(Takuto) What, what... Yes, yes, yes...

208
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:35,655
(Momoko) Minseok-san.

209
00:17:35,722 --> 00:17:37,657
Something happened earlier...

210
00:17:37,724 --> 00:17:39,726
(Minseok) Oh no.

211
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:50,670
(Ryo) Hey, Momoko-sensei. (Momoko) Huh?

212
00:17:50,737 --> 00:17:53,673
(Ryo) Which color do you think is good here?

213
00:17:53,740 --> 00:17:56,176
(Momoko) Wow~ During cherry blossom viewing?

214
00:17:56,242 --> 00:17:58,745
It was fun, wasn't it?

215
00:18:02,248 --> 00:18:05,118
>> I wanted to go again.

216
00:18:05,185 --> 00:18:09,622
(Takuto) Ryo Are you sane? You shouldn't ask Momoko about the painting.

217
00:18:09,689 --> 00:18:12,625
(Ryo) Yeah, I like Momoko-sensei's drawings.

218
00:18:12,692 --> 00:18:14,627
(Momoko) Ryo-kun is so kind.

219
00:18:14,694 --> 00:18:16,629
I mean, Takuto is also bad at drawing.

220
00:18:16,696 --> 00:18:18,631
(Takuto) I'm better than you. (Momoko) Say that →

221
00:18:18,698 --> 00:18:21,134
My summer vacation homework, even though my mom had me draw it.

222
00:18:21,201 --> 00:18:23,136
(Takuto) It's a rose! It’s you →

223
00:18:23,203 --> 00:18:25,138
I had my sister draw it every time.

224
00:18:25,205 --> 00:18:28,141
(Momoko) I drew it myself just by getting some advice.

225
00:18:28,208 --> 00:18:30,643
>> The more we fight, the better we get along.

226
00:18:30,710 --> 00:18:32,145
(Minseok) Huh?

227
00:18:32,212 --> 00:18:35,148
>> Those two have been together since childhood.

228
00:18:35,215 --> 00:18:37,150
(Minseok) Ah.

229
00:18:37,217 --> 00:18:41,154
>> I'm sure we'll continue to be together forever.

230
00:18:41,221 --> 00:18:43,156
Hahaha…｡

231
00:18:43,223 --> 00:18:44,657
(Momoko) The pink sheep is so cute.

232
00:18:44,724 --> 00:18:46,659
(Takuto) It's not about being cute or anything like that.

233
00:18:46,726 --> 00:18:49,162
(Momoko) Who thinks pink sheep are cute? Look!

234
00:18:49,229 --> 00:18:51,164
(Takuto) Isn't it strange that everyone was raising their hands?

235
00:18:51,231 --> 00:18:53,166
Because it's a mess... this person.

236
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:56,736
(Momoko) That's not true. (Takuto) Have you ever seen Pink Sheep?

237
00:19:08,781 --> 00:19:11,718
(Minseok) Thank you for your hard work.

238
00:19:11,784 --> 00:19:15,221
>>Ah, please leave me a suite →

239
00:19:15,288 --> 00:19:17,223
It really helped me.

240
00:19:17,290 --> 00:19:19,726
Immediately →

241
00:19:19,792 --> 00:19:23,229
Your reservation has been made.

242
00:19:23,296 --> 00:19:27,734
(Minseok) I'm sorry for staying so long.

243
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,802
>> Well…｡

244
00:19:31,804 --> 00:19:36,676
The break room is still part of the company's property, so →

245
00:19:36,743 --> 00:19:38,745
Don't forget.

246
00:20:13,279 --> 00:20:18,217
(Male) [This is the warmest restaurant in Tatekawa-cho]

247
00:20:18,284 --> 00:20:20,219
[Thank you] (Miki) [Thank you]

248
00:20:20,286 --> 00:20:23,222
[If you don't do it all the time, you'll be in trouble.]

249
00:20:23,289 --> 00:20:25,224
[troubled troubled]

250
00:20:25,291 --> 00:20:28,227
(Minseok) [Hey, everyone, it's okay] (Men) [Hmm? ]

251
00:20:28,294 --> 00:20:31,230
